<p>There is another reason investors use DCA: it matches the cadence of real life. Most households do not receive wealth in one large pile. They earn wages every two weeks, save monthly, and invest gradually through payroll deductions, retirement plans, and automatic index-fund purchases. In that sense, DCA is often less a strategy than a savings system.</p>
